## 4) Flow Files (Actual UI Actions + Assertions)

### Auth flows

#### `flows/auth/loginValid.flow.ts`
- Reads `email`, `password` from testcase input.
- Acknowledges splash, fills credentials, clicks login.
- Waits briefly and asserts URL contains `staff/appointments`.

#### `flows/auth/loginInvalidUsername.flow.ts`
- Reads invalid email + password.
- Attempts login.
- Uses `expectedData.message` fallbacking to `Invalid credentials`.
- Asserts error message visibility.

Note:
- Current `TC-AUTH-LOGIN-TC02.json` has `expectedData.errors[0].message` (nested), not `expectedData.message` (flat), so fallback text path is likely used unless data model is adjusted.

#### `flows/auth/loginInvalidPassword.flow.ts`
- Uses valid email + invalid password.
- Attempts login and asserts visible alert.

#### `flows/auth/loginLogout.flow.ts`
- Reuses `loginValid(...)` first (composition).
- Clicks profile text and logout icon.
- Asserts warning dialog appears.

Purpose of auth flows:
- Keep UI steps reusable and independently maintainable from orchestrator logic.

### User flows

#### `flows/Users/create.flow.ts`
- Reads user profile input fields.
- Fills name, DOB picker (year/month/day), email, reason, phone, state.
- Submits form.
- Locates user row by full name and handles 3 outcomes:
  - exactly 1 match -> assert visible,
  - more than 1 match -> assert first is visible,
  - none -> throw explicit error.

#### `flows/Users/delete.flow.ts`
- Quick-searches by `searchName`.
- Finds trash icons and handles count-based branching:
  - 1 icon -> click,
  - >1 -> click first,
  - 0 -> throw error.
- Confirms deletion and asserts success text.

#### `flows/Users/edituserpass.flow.ts`
- Searches user by name.
- Opens user details, navigates to password change action.
- Fills new password and submits.
- Asserts password-change confirmation text.

### Email flow

#### `flows/email/send.flow.ts`
- Opens New Message.
- Fills recipient search and selects match.
- Fills CC search and selects match.
- Fills subject + body.
- Sends message and asserts alert visibility.

