## 5) Module Config and Test Data Files

### Config files
- `data/json/modules/auth/config.json`
- `data/json/modules/user/config.json`
- `data/json/modules/email/config.json`

Each config provides:
- module metadata (`module`, `lastUpdated`, `description`),
- suite grouping (`smoke`, `regression`, `e2e`),
- testcase-id to file mapping (`testDataFiles`),
- tags grouping.

Critical role:
- These mappings are the source of truth for which JSON testcase files are executed.

### Testcase JSON files

Auth:
- `data/json/modules/auth/TC-AUTH-LOGIN-TC01.json` -> `flowKey: loginValid`
- `data/json/modules/auth/TC-AUTH-LOGIN-TC02.json` -> `flowKey: loginInvalidUsername`
- `data/json/modules/auth/TC-AUTH-LOGIN-TC03.json` -> `flowKey: loginInvalidPassword`
- `data/json/modules/auth/TC-AUTH-LOGIN-TC05.json` -> `flowKey: loginLogout`

User:
- `data/json/modules/user/TC-USER-01.json` -> `flowKey: createUser`
- `data/json/modules/user/TC-USER-02.json` -> `flowKey: deleteUser`
- `data/json/modules/user/TC-USER-03.json` -> `flowKey: editUserPassword`

Email:
- `data/json/modules/email/TC-EMAIL-01.json` -> `flowKey: sendEmail`

Common testcase schema includes:
- identity/metadata (`id`, `module`, `description`, `type`, `priority`, `suite`, `tags`),
- optional business narrative (`steps`, `expectedResult`),
- executable payload (`testData.input`, optional `testData.expectedData`).

